# Base URL for apps/studio-worker HTTP API (immersive-studio serve).
# Local direct: http://127.0.0.1:8787 (set STUDIO_CORS_ORIGINS on the worker for :5173).
# Local via Vite proxy (same-origin, no CORS): create .env.development.local with:
#   VITE_STUDIO_API_PROXY=1
# In `npm run dev`, that proxy flag overrides VITE_STUDIO_API_URL so a production URL in `.env`
# does not send the browser to the live site by mistake.
# Production: set before `vite build` — VITE_* is inlined at compile time.
# VITE_STUDIO_API_URL=https://api.immersivelabs.space
#
# Worker must list your site origin(s) in STUDIO_CORS_ORIGINS when not using the proxy, e.g.
#   https://immersivelabs.space,https://www.immersivelabs.space
VITE_STUDIO_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787

# --- Production (Cloudflare Pages) checklist ---
# 1. Cloudflare Dashboard → Workers & Pages → your Pages project → Settings → Environment variables:
#    set VITE_STUDIO_API_URL to your public worker HTTPS origin (no trailing slash), e.g. https://api.yourdomain.com
# 2. Trigger a new production deployment so Vite inlines that URL into the bundle.
# 3. On the worker VM/container: STUDIO_CORS_ORIGINS must list every origin users type in the browser (apex, www, *.pages.dev previews if you use them). See docs/studio/deploy-gcp-free-vm.md
# 4. After pulling Python worker changes: rebuild/restart the Docker container (or process) on the API host — not just Pages. Confirm GET /api/studio/health returns worker_version.

# --- Private Fab plugin zips (/p/plugins/*) ---
# Optional. If set, /p/plugins pages require this passphrase (stored in sessionStorage for the tab).
# Leave empty for unlisted-URL-only pages (zips must still be copied into public — see sync-fab-plugin-zips-to-web.ps1).
# VITE_PRIVATE_PLUGIN_DL_PASSWORD=

# --- Public Fab plugin zips (/fab-products, /p/plugins download buttons) ---
# Production: zips are gitignored and are usually NOT in the Vite build. Set this so links
# point at an external static host (R2, GitHub Release assets, S3) instead of 404ing on same origin.
# Example (GitHub Release with tag "ue5.7-2024" after uploading the five *-UE5.7-Win64.zip files):
#   VITE_FAB_MARKETPLACE_ZIP_BASE=https://github.com/OWNER/REPO/releases/download/ue5.7-2024
# Local dev: leave unset and run scripts/sync-fab-plugin-zips-to-web.ps1 so public/plugin-packages/ has files.
# VITE_FAB_MARKETPLACE_ZIP_BASE=
